bpm (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low

    * Added `ini/parser.sh` a utility to parse contents of ini files into arrays.
    * Added Main application "options" to list of suggestions for auto-completion.
    * Added [Bats](https://github.com/bats-core/bats-core) testing framework and initialised a testing setup.
    * Added `str/trim.sh` string trim utility.
    * Added `str/pos.sh` string character position utility.
    * Removed `distribution/debian/files` file. This is generated on each build and will therefore no longer be tracked.

 -- Alin Eugen Deac <aedart@gmail.com>  Sun, 01 May 2022 13:50:00 +0200

bpm (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

    * Added Bash auto-completion for `bpm` binary.
    * Changed `version` command is now able to show current "dev" version, while application is located within a git repository
    * Changed Improved `bin/build-version` helper. It's now able to obtain "dev" version, when current commit does match that of the git tag's commit.
    * Changed Support for `NO_COLOR` environment variable. If set, then output will remove ANSI colour codes.
    * Fixed ANSI not entirely removed in `output_helpers::resolve_ansi` method

 -- Alin Eugen Deac <aedart@gmail.com>  Fri, 15 Apr 2022 15:36:42 +0200

bpm (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initialisation of project, top-level directory structure, changelog, license...etc
  * Core cli application architecture for invoking commands with eventual options
  * ANSI output utilities
  * `bin/build` helper to build debian package
  * `bin/build-version` helper to build a `version` text file
  * `docs/maintainer` preliminary maintainer documentation

 -- Alin Eugen Deac <aedart@gmail.com>  Wed, 13 Apr 2022 18:19:02 +0200
